# SeeSaw Cloud Agent — Technical Architecture Blueprint (Tier 3)

## Overview

The `seesaw-cloud-agent` is the **enhancement and intelligence amplification layer** of the SeeSaw system. Tier 2 (iPhone + Apple Foundation Models) handles the complete interactive story loop for all children — it works fully offline. Tier 3 exists to make stories **richer, longer, more memorable, and shareable**. It also provides the parent dashboard, community story wall, analytics, and the long-term memory that makes Whisper feel like it knows the child over weeks and months. 

The key design principle: **Tier 3 never blocks the child**. The iOS app never waits for a Tier 3 response before speaking. All cloud calls happen asynchronously in the background. The child always hears something within 1 second — from the on-device Apple Foundation Model — and Tier 3 enriches what happens next.

***

## 1. System Role & Responsibilities

### What Tier 3 Does

| Responsibility | Description | Technology |
|---|---|---|
| **Enhanced story beats** | Richer, longer Gemini 2.0 Flash story segments for "enhanced mode" | Google ADK + Gemini 2.0 Flash |
| **Long-term child memory** | Remembers favourite characters, themes, story arcs across sessions | Firestore `child_profiles` collection |
| **Session persistence** | Every story turn is saved; sessions resumable across days | Firestore `sessions` + `beats` collections |
| **Parent dashboard** | Real-time view of sessions, transcripts, engagement metrics | Firestore real-time listeners |
| **Story wall** | Community feed of completed, parent-approved stories | Firestore `published_stories` + Cloud Storage |
| **Parental controls sync** | Server-side topic restrictions, safety policy updates | Firestore `parent_config` + Remote Config |
| **Apple Intelligence sync** | Receives `StoryBeat` context summaries from on-device FM for continuity | REST endpoint `/sync/beat` |
| **Safety audit log** | Every beat logged for safety review and research analysis | Firestore `safety_logs` |
| **Analytics** | Story completion rates, engagement per age group, object → theme mappings | BigQuery + Firebase Analytics |

### What Tier 3 Does NOT Do
- Block story playback (async only)
- Store raw images, audio, or faces (only text labels from Tier 2 privacy pipeline)
- Handle BLE communication (Tier 1 responsibility)
- Run the core interactive loop (Tier 2 Apple FM responsibility)

