## 8. Google Cloud TTS Integration

Tier 3 generates professional-quality audio for enhanced beats using Google Cloud TTS, which the iOS app can optionally download and play instead of `AVSpeechSynthesizer`.

```python
from google.cloud import texttospeech

def synthesise_beat(text: str, child_age: int) -> str:
    client = texttospeech.TextToSpeechClient()
    
    # Age-appropriate voice selection
    voice_name = "en-US-Journey-F" if child_age <= 6 else "en-US-Neural2-F"
    
    synthesis_input = texttospeech.SynthesisInput(
        ssml=f"""<speak>
            <prosody rate="85%" pitch="+2st">
                {text}
            </prosody>
        </speak>"""
    )
    
    voice = texttospeech.VoiceSelectionParams(
        language_code="en-US",
        name=voice_name
    )
    
    audio_config = texttospeech.AudioConfig(
        audio_encoding=texttospeech.AudioEncoding.MP3
    )
    
    response = client.synthesize_speech(
        input=synthesis_input, voice=voice, audio_config=audio_config
    )
    
    # Upload to Cloud Storage, return signed URL (1hr expiry)
    url = upload_to_storage(response.audio_content, session_id, turn_number)
    return url
```

The iOS `CloudAgentService` downloads this URL and caches the MP3 locally. If the URL is available before the child asks the next question, the enhanced Cloud TTS voice plays instead of `AVSpeechSynthesizer`.

