## 9. Parent Dashboard Data Model

The iOS companion app reads directly from Firestore using Firebase SDK (no additional API needed):

```swift
// In seesaw-companion-ios: ParentDashboardViewModel.swift
func fetchSessions(childId: String) {
    db.collection("seesaw/sessions")
        .whereField("child_id", isEqualTo: childId)
        .order(by: "started_at", descending: true)
        .limit(to: 20)
        .addSnapshotListener { [weak self] snapshot, error in
            self?.sessions = snapshot?.documents.compactMap {
                try? $0.data(as: SessionSummary.self)
            } ?? []
        }
}
```

Real-time updates mean the parent app shows new turns appearing live as the child plays.

