## 10. Story Publishing Workflow

When a parent approves sharing, a Cloud Functions trigger fires:

```
Firestore: sessions/{id} status → "publishing_requested"
       │
       ▼
Cloud Function: onPublishRequested
       │
       ├── Call Gemini to generate story title + summary
       ├── Assemble full_text from all beats subcollection
       ├── Run final safety check
       ├── Write to published_stories collection
       └── Firestore: sessions/{id} status → "published"
```

The iOS app's "Story Wall" tab reads from `published_stories`, ordered by `published_at`, with region filtering for a localised community feel.

