## 12. Security Model

| Layer | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| iOS → Tier 3 auth | Firebase Auth JWT token in `Authorization: Bearer` header |
| Rate limiting | `slowapi` — 100 beats/day per child_id |
| PII guardrail | Tier 3 rejects any request containing raw images, audio, or face data |
| Data residency | Firestore multi-region (nam5) — data stays in North America/EU |
| Child data protection | COPPA-aligned — child profiles contain no PII beyond age + first name |
| Story publishing | Requires explicit parent Firebase Auth token + `share_enabled: true` in `parent_config` |
| Audit trail | Every beat, every safety event, every publish action logged with timestamp |

